meaningMnemonic: An <kanji>aviation</kanji> (航空) <kanji>mother</kanji> <kanji>warship</kanji> is a warship that is like mother to all the aviation things (the airplanes). They come home to their mother warship, which is an <vocabulary>aircraft carrier</vocabulary>.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word that uses the on'yomi readings of the kanji. You should be able to read this on your own.
